    <section id="jats_dragdrop_actions">
      <title>JATS Drag/Drop Actions</title>
      <p id="p_bqk_cgk_54b">Dragging a file from the <xref href="using-the-project-view.dita#using-the-project-view"
          format="dita"><uicontrol product="author editor">Project</uicontrol><uicontrol
            product="authorEclipse editorEclipse">Project Explorer</uicontrol> view</xref> and
        dropping it into a JATS document that is edited in <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode,
        creates a link to the dragged file (the <xmlelement>ext-link</xmlelement> element with the
          <xmlatt>xlink:href</xmlatt> attribute) at the drop location. Dragging an image file from
        the default file system application (Windows Explorer on Windows or Finder on macOS, for
        example) and dropping it into a JATS document inserts an image element (the
          <xmlelement>inline-graphic</xmlelement> element with the <xmlatt>xlink:href</xmlatt>
        attribute) at the drop location, similar to the <uicontrol>Insert Image</uicontrol> toolbar
        action.</p>
